summary: What about little piece of Harry choosing the ring for y/n? And maybe niall helps him with that? He gets nervous because it's a...
question: What about little piece of Harry choosing the ring for y/n? And maybe niall helps him with that? He gets nervous because it's a lot of rings and he don't know which one will be perfect
answer:
I tried to make this funny and cute 😂 i really did. I just really love Narry okay?

.

“Why couldn’t you ask Layla to come with you? I don’t know anything about jewelry!”

“Because Layla cannot keep a secret!” Harry wraps an arm around his best friend’s shoulder as they walk into the store. “No offense but tell your girlfriend a secret and the next day the whole world will know about it.”

“Actually I’m not offended at all.” Niall heaves a sigh, nodding his head. “She was the reason everyone in our high school knew I had a teddy bear named Lion in my locker.”

Harry stops immediately to look at Niall with his eyebrows furrowed and mouth agape. “You had a teddy bear named Lion in your locker? Why?!”

“Because I wanted a lion but my mum gave me a bear for my 7th birthday alright! Stop being so fucking judgmental!”

Harry intends to make a joke to embarrass his friend but as soon as he opens his mouth he gets interrupted by one of the staff in the store that approaches them.

“Hi, can I help you?” Says the friendly lady with a great smile.

“Uhm, I’m looking for an engagement ring,” replies Harry.

The woman takes a look at both him and Niall before telling them to come with her inside to check out a few available models. Harry’s not entirely foreign to this, after all he did help his stepfather pick out a ring for his mother. He knows what to do, and how to do it. Niall, on the other hand, has never been to a place like this so he keeps looking around with his eyes widened and mouth in an ‘o’ shape, just like Alice arriving in Wonderland.

The lady shows them all the good options they have in the store, briefly explains the price range, and the quality of each. Then something suddenly comes up and she has to excuse herself to run inside for a minute, leaving the boys back with a bunch of rings to choose from.

“Do you even know her size?” Niall asks, a bit mortified by all these sparkly objects in front of him.

“Yeah, I wore the promise ring on my pinky and it fits her ring finger so,” says Harry as he gives Niall his hand and the best friend knows exactly what to do. He puts each ring on Harry’s pinky, waits for Harry to say no then moves on to the next one. It takes him a few nos to finally find one that he’s actually satisfied with, just in time the lady returns.

“I’m sorry…Something came up. Have you found something you like?”

“Yeah, this one.” Harry gives her the ring of his choice, smiling from ear to ear.

“This one is very beautiful.” Then she turns to Niall. “You’re lucky, your fiancé has a sophisticated eye.”

Harry and Niall exchange looks, and at the same time, burst into laughter. Their reactions confuse the poor lady who has no idea what she said that they found so hilarious.

“See, love? I told you I should handle our wedding decorations,” Harry says to Niall, who’s covering his face while trying not to laugh and his face actually turns bright red because of it. The lady still doesn’t get it, she just assumes they have a weird sense of humor and carries on with explaining the payment procedures.

When they leave the store with the ring, Niall says to his best friend, “I can’t believe we just cheated on our girlfriends with each other.”

“I can’t believe you had a teddy bear named Lion.”

“Fuck I knew I shouldn’t have told you that, you dickhead!” Niall grumbles as they reach Harry’s car parked out front.

Harry intends to get in but hesitates and stands there with one hand on top of the opened car door. “Hey man.”

“Yeah?” Niall gives his friend a look.

“What if she says no?”

Harry’s question gets Niall to snort. “She’s not gonna say no. She loves you.”

“You sure?”

“Yeah I’m sure. Don’t worry man, she’ll say yes in a heartbeat.” Niall gives Harry an encouraging smile before he adds, “if she says no, I’ll marry you. I’m sure that ring will fit one of my fingers.”

Niall observing his own hand makes Harry chuckle. He shakes his head and calls his best friend an idiot, but honestly, he doesn’t think he’ll ever find a friend as great as Niall.
